The population decline continued throughout the 20th century, dwindling to 275 by 1950.

The [[United States 2000 Census|2000 census]] showed 440 people, 221 households, and 118 families resided in the Goldfield [[census county division]].  The [[Race (United States Census)|racial makeup]] of the CCD was 93.2% White, 0.2% Black or African American, 2.0% Native American, 0.2% Pacific Islander, 1.4% from other races, and 3.0% from two or more races.  About 5.2% of the population was Hispanic or Latino of any race.

